description: Superman fights the Martians from the H. G. Wells novel The War of the Worlds.

Co-feature art by Travis Moore and Dan Green Cover by Freddie Williams II

In "Constellations" part 2, the All-Stars are on the trail of the villains who've kidnapped one of their own while internal turmoil creates drama in the ranks! And after what went down in the JSA ANNUAL this month, it looks like Magog won't be on the team much longer!

In the co-feature, Liberty Belle and Hourman trek to Venice alongside Icicle and Tigress in an amazing race to learn the secret of the ancient Staff of Legends!

description:
In the business of arms dealing, your list of enemies is as long as your list of clients. And if that isn't enough to make you sleep with a gun under your pillow, the thought of being under government surveillance might! Someone has to put a hit on Koko, and a pair of ruthless assassins make its move. But Koko Hekmatyar and her squad are a very hard target--trained pros know, when you get ambushed, the best way out of the kill zone is to attack!

Zoichi and his transhuman allies have no time to waste; the countdown to the zombie apocalypse has begun!

Chatting with his friends from the bar in Manaus, Mister No recalls his adventure in Arizona, when he was a guest on the immense ranch of the millionaire John Trevor. A western epic fanatic, Trevor organized a pretend stagecoach hold-up as a welcome for Jerry, but fiction becomes reality
name: Ombre Rosse

description: 1910. Julio Cesar Cabral is nominated Emperor. He is the greatest rubber magnate in the Amazon and enjoys torturing the poor Indios. As for his son Francisco, he shows unusual mental powers, to the point where he seems to be possessed by the devil. And, forty years later, followed by CIA agents, he meets Mister No
name: La Casa di Satana

description: A young Indian has been killed during the fake stagecoach hold-up, organized by the eccentric millionaire Trevor. Intending to discover who, among the guests at the ranch, is the murderer, Mister No follows a trail that takes him to a mysterious ghost-town lost deep in the mountains
name: Il Marchio dell'Assassino

description: While another death is added to the list, Mister No pursues his investigations on Mister Trevors ranch, helped by the bizarre Sheriff Ford and by the amicable Indio Hokahei.. He discovers the incredible solution to the caseso incredible that not even his friends, to whom he is telling the story, believe it!
name: La Fine della Pista

description: Hit by a mysterious flying object, Mister No crashes with his Piper in the jungle. Some natives subject him to arcane rites. They are about kill him, when Jerry is saved bya Soviet astronaut who has landed in the forest!
name: Alien!

description: The Petn is a desolate region in Central America. Mister No, Esse-Esse and Patricia have arrived here, following a scientific expedition. The group find a very interesting archaeological site, but they have to confront ferocious bandits and General Duartes men
name: Il Sepolcro Indiano

description: The Zambos, i.e. the mad General Juan Ximil Duartes men, attack the archaeological ruins that Duarte considers sacred because his son has been buried there. Mister No, Esse-Esse, Patricia and the other components of the expedition have to escape into the jungle, chased by the Zambos!
name: Il Re della Giungla

description: "Nova Mad Mary": this is the name of the company headed by Senhor Galvao, who wants to construct a railway in the jungle, after the miserably failed attempt undertaken by others at the beginning of the century.. Mister No with his client Almeida, a seedy journalist, visits an tribe of Indios, whom Nova Mad Marys men are subjecting to ruthless harassment
name: La Legge della Violenza

description: By now full-blown war has broken out between Mister No and the Nova Mad Mary Company. What is more, Jerry discovers that Galvao does not really want to construct a railway in the Amazons, but instead wants to recover a chest of gold coins, hidden by his father to cheat the insurance company. And Almeida is certainly not a journalist
name: Caccia all'Uomo

description: Mister No is a tour guide on a cruise in the Caribbean. He flirts with the beautiful Lana, laughing at the luckless advances of Sailor, a braggart Everything would appear to be rolling along smoothly, if it were not for the mysterious Mister Meyer and for an inexplicable crime that suddenly disrupts life on board!
name: Una Notte a Trinidad

description: Professor Thompson has been murdered by Meyer, who, in reality, is a gangster. Meyer also kills Sailer, an Interpol agent, and kidnaps Lana. Mister No is accused of murder, but he is helped by a warrior (who introduces Che Guevara to him!) and by Monsieur Bagarre, a strange French pilot
name: Allarme a Bordo

description: Fog Peak: a mountain that conceals a fabulous diamond mine. Greedy for this treasure, the sinister Big Bag convinces the palaeontologist Alex Titius that there are dinosaur fossils to be found on Fog Peak. Therefore, Titius organises an expedition to recover them, hiring Big Bang as a guide
name: Il Picco delle Nebbie

description: China: 184 A.D., a time of great turmoil. A young drifter names Zhang Fei stumbles upon a slaughtered village and encounters the volunteer army of Liu Bei. He joins them in time to help in the defense of the walled city. But he's stuck by an arrow and thrown off a cliff. Rescued by two wizards, he is revived and given great powers. But the price could cost him his very soul!
name: Vol. 1

description: Evils abound when ex-roommates seek revenge, alien head lice invade, supervillains come out of the closet, and the homeless attack! The purchase of this issue is guaranteed to enhance your sex life and make your estranged parents apologize for a trauma-filled childhood. The perfect jumping-on point for new readers!
While Wilson Fisk makes his move on the leading crime families of New York, Frank Castle has problems of his own. Namely the sledgehammer-swinging hitman known as The Mennonite.
name: Kingpin, Part 4

description: There is one villain who can make Moon Knight look sane: The Scarecrow. This unhinged lunatic has taken to the streets. Now Moon Knight must face the Scarecrow and his minions of madness under a black sky filled with crows in this final obstacle keeping him from his true nemesis: Bushman.
name: Shock and Awe: Chapter 5: Past is Prologue

description:
Black Lantern Superboy targets the love of his life--Wonder Girl! Can she drag the Boy of Steel back from the brink of insanity?

Blackest Night Tie-in

Conner's body has been taken over by a Black Lantern and in currently fighting Cassie. Meanwhile inside Conner's mind, the true Conner fights to take back control of his body.

Conner is able to take control long enough to whistle for Krypto and give Cassie one word, "Fortress". Cassie gets the hint and tricks Black Lantern Conner to follow her and Krypto to the Fortress of Solitude.

There Krypto, senses Conner's body, which was put into the Kryptonian Healing Chamber by the Legion. Krypto then digs up the camber while Cassie battles Black Lantern Conner and the real Conner tries to break the Black Lantern Rings control.

When Conner's body is brought above ground the ring is confused and leaves Conner's body and tries to go onto the dead Conner's body, but Conner freezes it and Cassie throws it deep into space.

Conner, Cassie, and Krypto head back to Coast city to help defeat the Black Lanterns still there.

Continued in Blackest Night #8
name: What Did Black Lantern Superboy Do?

description: Picking up right where the first ATOM EVE miniseries left off! See the secret origin of Rex Splode! See what shaped him into the man who tragically sacrificed himself in the Invincible War. Don't miss the stunning conclusion to this hit miniseries!

volume.name: Invincible Presents: Atom Eve & Rex Splode
